title: Chicago XI (11)
description:
This was the last album before Terry Kath died.  Pretty ironic, I&#039;ve always thought, because one of his last songs, "Little One" was written to his daughter in which he says, "I will always be there."  And then he blows his brains out -- accidentally people insist, and it seems believable that he was just careless.

It&#039;s also the last album with long-time producer James William Guercio.  Which seems okay because the sound was pretty much played by this time.  Elektra Glide in Blue didn&#039;t help, either.

On this album:

Mississippi Delta City Blues

Baby, What a Big Surprise

Till the End of Time

Policeman

Take Me Back to Chicago

Vote For Me

Takin&#039; It On Uptown

This Time

The Inner Struggle of a Man

Prelude (Little One)

Little One

Wish I Could Fly

Paris
